==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[relativus]]'', adjective form with suffix ''[[-ivus]]'', from ''[[relatus]]'', perfect passive participle of ''[[referre]]'', lit. '''carry again''', from prefix ''[[re-]]'', '''again''' + ''[[ferre]]'', '''bear''' or '''carry''', from PIE ??


===Preposition===

#Relating to, being relevant towards.

===Adjective===
'''relative'''

# not [[absolute]]; connected to or depending on something else
# of the Theory of Relativity. (usually with capital R)
#: 'Time travel is not possible due to current relative laws.'

